        <abstract>
            <p>CD has read the two reports on culture of poppies with interest and has planted seeds.</p>
            <p>Suggests an experiment for evidence on whether plants, thought merely varieties, are like species and fail to intercross, despite insect pollination.</p>
        </abstract>
